com.samsung.android.sdk.mediacontrol

Interface SmcImageViewer.ResponseListener

  • Enclosing interface:
    SmcImageViewer

    public static interface SmcImageViewer.ResponseListener
    This listener interface provides callback methods for response events.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onHide(SmcImageViewer device, int error)
      Called when the response for SmcImageViewer.hide() is received.

      Called when the response for SmcImageViewer.requestStateInfo() is received.

    • Method Detail

      • onShow

        void onShow(SmcImageViewer device,
          SmcItem smcItem,
          int error)
        Called when the response for SmcImageViewer.show(SmcItem) is received.
        Parameters:
        device - The image viewer instance.
        smcItem - The image being shown.
        error - The event status description. The valid values are:
        • Smc.ERROR_BAD_RESPONSE
        • Smc.ERROR_UNKNOWN
        • Smc.ERROR_FEATURE_NOT_SUPPORTED
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_ARGUMENT
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_OBJECT
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_STATE
        • Smc.ERROR_ITEM_NOT_EXIST
        • Smc.ERROR_NETWORK_NOT_AVAILABLE
        • Smc.ERROR_NO_RESPONSE
        • Smc.ERROR_OUT_OF_MEMORY
        • Smc.ERROR_PERMISSION_NOT_ALLOWED
        • Smc.ERROR_SERVICE_NOT_CONNECTED
        • Smc.ERROR_TIME_OUT
        • Smc.SUCCESS

      • onRequestStateInfo

        void onRequestStateInfo(SmcImageViewer device,
                      int state,
                      int error)
        Called when the response for SmcImageViewer.requestStateInfo() is received.
        Parameters:
        device - The image viewer instance.
        state - The image viewer state. The valid values are:
        • SmcImageViewer.IMAGE_VIEWER_STATE_BUFFERING
        • SmcImageViewer.IMAGE_VIEWER_STATE_CONTENT_CHANGED
        • SmcImageViewer.IMAGE_VIEWER_STATE_HIDDEN
        • SmcImageViewer.IMAGE_VIEWER_STATE_SHOWING
        • SmcImageViewer.IMAGE_VIEWER_STATE_UNKNOWN
        If the response fails, this value is set to SmcImageViewer.IMAGE_VIEWER_STATE_UNKNOWN
        error - The event status description. The valid values are:
        • Smc.ERROR_BAD_RESPONSE
        • Smc.ERROR_UNKNOWN
        • Smc.ERROR_FEATURE_NOT_SUPPORTED
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_ARGUMENT
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_OBJECT
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_STATE
        • Smc.ERROR_ITEM_NOT_EXIST
        • Smc.ERROR_NETWORK_NOT_AVAILABLE
        • Smc.ERROR_NO_RESPONSE
        • Smc.ERROR_OUT_OF_MEMORY
        • Smc.ERROR_PERMISSION_NOT_ALLOWED
        • Smc.ERROR_SERVICE_NOT_CONNECTED
        • Smc.ERROR_TIME_OUT
        • Smc.SUCCESS
